cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper presents a conversational agent that draws on human conversational strategies to combine commands, allowing it to perform more complex tasks. This involves the use of natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also focuses on the evaluation of the agent's performance in a data science domain, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the design of a conversational type system that manages what kinds of commands can be combined, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
